parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The misalignment of the steering system and vibration can cause the vehicle to wander or drift while driving, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents or loss of vehicle stability.
symptoms: The vehicle wanders or drifts while driving on a straight road
the steering wheel cannot be centered
the steering wheel and front driver-side seat vibrate while driving at certain speeds
the vehicle clunks and lurches forward when approaching a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Spongy Brake Pedal and Intermittent Brake Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spongy brake pedal and intermittent brake failure can cause a loss of braking power, leading to increased stopping distances, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor with little or no resistance
the vehicle slows down slightly but does not come to a complete stop
the brake pedal has a delayed response to braking input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake pedal failure to return to its normal position can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal remains stuck to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position after being pressed
the vehicle is unable to be driven safely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive glare from high-intensity headlights can cause temporary blindness, distraction, and discomfort to other drivers, pedestrians, and cyclists, increasing the risk of accidents and road rage incidents.
symptoms: Excessive glare from oncoming or following vehicles
especially from larger pickup trucks
causing temporary blindness
discomfort
or distraction; difficulty seeing the road ahead or surrounding environment; need to adjust or avoid looking at rearview mirrors to reduce glare.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster/dashboard electronics can cause a range of issues, including malfunctioning radio, incorrect date and time, loss of radio programs, and faulty dimming controls, which can be distracting and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The dashboard electronics reset
the radio malfunctions
the date and time are incorrect
radio programs are lost
dimming controls do not function properly
unknown other issues may occur.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the radio can cause frustration and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents or decreased driver attention.
symptoms: The radio turns off for periods of time
the radio does not work at all
the radio works only occasionally
the radio has poor reception or sound quality.
